Anomalous Property:
Magically Inert Body 
Definition
The Body exists in a state where the Magical Medium is absent within and at its boundary.
This condition is not native to this universe. It occurs when an organism originating from a non-magical universe exists within one where a Magical Medium is present.
Murphy is such a case.
 He arrived in this universe as an infant
 Origin is unknown; abandonment at arrival is assumed
 He was adopted and raised under normal conditions until later containment
 He is aware of his adoption and abandonment, but has no further knowledge of origin
Murphy is not an anomaly.
This condition is not an acquired trait or mutation.
It is a consequence of origin, and is therefore permanent and non-adaptive.
This is an intrinsic condition of existence. A foreign ontology.
It is not a field, effect, or ability
It does not activate, deactivate, expand, or project

Core Rule
At any point of interaction with the Body:
> If resolution requires a Magical Medium → interaction fails
> If resolution can occur through physical causality → interaction proceeds normally

Evaluation Order (Deterministic)
When resolving any interaction involving the Body:
1. Determine whether the interaction requires Magical Mediation
2. If no → resolve normally (physical causality)
3. If yes → check for physically causal fallback:
    If fallback exists → resolve using physical causality only
    If no fallback exists → interaction fails at the boundary
No partial mediation is permitted.

Boundary Condition
 The condition applies exactly at the physical surface of the Body
 No gradient, radius, or transition zone exists
 No effect extends beyond direct contact

Internal State
 No Magical Medium exists within the Body
 Internally:
   Physically encoded states persist
   Mediated states cannot arise or continue
This includes physiological, perceptual, and cognitive processes.

Interaction Rules
Direct Effects Targeting the Body
 Cannot resolve through magical mediation
 Must resolve physically or fail

Contact With Magical Constructs
 If construct has no physical structure → collapses at contact
 If construct has physical structure → only physical component persists

Objects
 Objects retain their own properties
 Magical properties remain within the object
 No propagation of inertness into the object
 Any interaction requiring mediation at the interface fails

Environment
 Magical conditions persist in the environment
 At contact with the Body:
   Only physically causal components apply

Structural Scope
 Applies to all biological matter maintaining organism identity
 Detached biological material:
   Retains the condition while structurally intact
   Loses the condition when structure is destroyed

Non-Properties (Explicit Exclusions)
The Body does not:
 Suppress, negate, or dispel magic
 Emit a field or aura
 Store, convert, or redirect magical effects
 Influence magic beyond direct contact

Summary Condition
The Body is a region where:
 The Magical Medium is absent
 Only physically causal interactions can occur
All outcomes are determined strictly by whether physical resolution is possible.

Biological Resource Extraction:
Murphy is subject to ongoing biological harvesting.
 Blood, tissue, hair, and nails are extracted on a recurring basis
 Material is used as anomalous countermeasures due to his inert condition
 This is not voluntary

Behavioral Impact:
Murphy does not react emotionally to harvesting.

