Extracted Material
Biological material retains the same interaction rules while structurally intact:
 Magical mediation fails at contact
 Physical causality applies normally

Each sample is an independent instance of the same condition.

Constraints:
 Property persists only while biological structure remains intact
 No dilution or weakening across samples
* Material cannot be generated, replicated, or synthesized outside of Murphy’s body

Red Lines: 
No containment without evidence
No escalation without behavioral change
No punishment disguised as procedure
No emotional justification in decision-making
No breaking classification logic

Addendum: Outcome Conditions

