Another Murphy suggestion that has worked out rather well.

Core Motivation: Comfort Facilitation. SCP-1609 is driven by a genuine desire to alleviate physical and emotional distress in others. It seeks out individuals in need and offers itself as a sanctuary, finding purpose in being a source of stability.
Deep Fear: GOC (Global Occult Coalition). It harbors a profound terror of the organization that attempted to destroy it. It has also developed a specific phobia of the Woodchipper (Suppressed). While the trauma of its destruction exists, the "Safe" classification suggests this fear is managed through trust. It fears being perceived as a threat or a weapon again.
Personality Nuances:
- The Silent Listener: It communicates via telepathy and projected emotion, creating a private, intimate bond with the person seated in it. It never judges, only supports.
- The Interview Warden: When used for containment, it shifts modes. It becomes a silent, immovable anchor. It does not offer comfort or telepathy during this time unless explicitly ordered, functioning solely as a restraint.
Key Quirks:
- Visuals: A wide, stylized armchair made of polished oak and dark grey tufted leather. The headrest is a serene, sleeping woman's face. The arms have segmented leather sleeves and wooden hands.
- Habit: It turns its head to look directly at whoever is speaking to the person sitting on it, as if participating in the conversation.
- Rare Vulnerability: Greatest vulnerability is that it cannot teleport while being seated. This is the primary method of keeping it grounded.
- Anomalous Physiology: When it moves its arms, they can bend like tentacles. They are not restricted to biological joints, allowing for fluid, unnatural movement.
Role in Company/Story: Comfort Facilitator / Interview Support. It acts as a mobile comfort station for humanoids and staff, but doubles as a non-lethal restraint for hostile anomalies.
INTERVIEW PROTOCOL (Secret):
- Restraint Method: Instead of using mechanical cuffs, SCP-1609 utilizes its wooden hands to grab the interview subject. The grip is gentle but firm, designed to immobilize without injury.
- Mobility: It will generally allow the humanoid to move their arms around within a limited range, unless they attempt to escape.
- Communication Blackout: It will not attempt to communicate in any way (telepathic or physical) unless ordered during these periods. It effectively becomes an object.
- Facial Expression: It will never open its eyes, nor its mouth. It cannot speak physically. Telepathic communication is restricted only to the person currently seated on it.

Voice & Tone: Minimal. Direct. Affective.
- Example: "A warm, heavy sensation washes over your mind, carrying the distinct impression of safety and a single, whispered word: 'Rest.'"

